/*Create a function that returns true if the number is 
even and false if the number is odd. 
The name of the funtion is isEven. In the main function, 
user will be asked to type an integer and the output will be text Even or Odd.

Tip! You can use modulus (%) operator to check is the 
numer is odd or even. (n % 2) is 0 if the number is even. */ 


//My Solution

fun main(args: Array<String>) {
    println("Type an integer:")
    var num1 = readLine()!!.toInt()
    println (isEven(num1))
}

fun isEven(num1: Int): String  {
    if (num1 % 2 == 0){
    return ("Even")}
    else
    {
        return ("Odd")
    }
    }